				<div class="message">Out of curiosity, how do you feel about game programming teaching bad software programming practices?  I feel like most people I meet in the software development world who come from game development backgrounds and fairly universal in their admission that games are generally not programmed well from a software perspective.  But I probably have a biased group of people who I can ask about such issues.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I think they are many times badly programmed due to deadlines,  Games have much tighter deadlines than any other software made.  It is far easier to delay productivity software or an OS than it is a game because non-games do not have market windows to meet.   Nobody thinks &quot;Would it be great to get the next version of Office out in time for christmas&quot;,  If a version of an OS is delayed a year nobody gives a shit,  There are no fans of operating systems like video game fans.
