				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Game Programming
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1831585">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Wool</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=ef035035ca80ac30c4a1f3dbbb883709&amp;p=1831540#post1831540" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Boy, that was something. I'll refrain from asking what you were under the influence of while typing all that. <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<img src="images/smilies/monkeydance.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Dance Like a Monkey!" class="inlineimg" /></div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>The ludicrous part is how plausible it is; testing these hypotheses out in the real world is why I want to start my own K-12 school within the next ten years. It's part of what I am allocating my profits toward. I think I can cut out all the fat in K-12, adopting some of the behaviors of a magnet school amongst other things, and reduce K-12 education time to about a third of what it is and at &lt; 1/10th the cost. I reject that I am somehow special in being able to learn from online courses well. Additionally, while they have an incredibly bad reputation for good reasons, I intend to start my own town using it as a proof of concept for the larger US region. <br />
<br />
While I know my ideas are sound, people are wont to criticize and dismiss out of hand anything that does not fit into their local cable news memes, so, like with my business I have to make it undeniably factual such that it is reasonable to dismiss out of hand people who claim they are false. Still that is not enough, there are ample models for other aspects of society that are eschewed in favor of wasteful ineffective programs, so I also have to determine how to circumvent emotional biases. Another reason I want to start my own town is that there does not exist any in the US that I want to actually live in, also it is surprising how much autonomy towns have as a government. <br />
<br />
Of course I could simply emigrate elsewhere, I had considered doing so a great deal, but then I lose the ability to run a business with as little initial capital as possible. While the US sucks in a lot of ways, it is excellent for corporations. I was not joking when I said that a Panopticon is an exceptionally good idea for society when it is ran with the right ambitions in mind. Myself, I have my entire house and land under surveillance, mainly this is derived from protecting myself against false accusations or counterfactual claims in the event of my untimely death or attempts to blackmail those around me, but it has other ancillary benefits as well. Additionally, my vehicles are similarly under constant surveillance, primarily because cops are extraordinarily untrustworthy and can eat a bag of 16&quot; dicks until they choke and die like the trifling bitches they are.<br />
<br />
As a trivial example, it is my ongoing hypothesis that most social problems are made irrelevant or sourced in the individuals in question not having gotten properly fucked frequently enough, being unhealthy, or being abused at work, all of which are resolvable given proper governance in those aspects; I think I could drastically reduce the divorce rate simply by promoting open marriages successfully and removing social stigmas regarding fucking and kinks. I don't think it is at all unreasonable that self-exploration should be diminished, in fact most memes are ludicrous in all aspects, such as slut shaming, which is sourced in motivations that are no longer relevant in the context of modern medicine. Orgasms for everyone.<br />
<br />
Of course people can claim I am crazy and dangerous for humanity, it's not that difficult to support such a claim, it's far bolder though to test if they are actually true though rather than backseat drive into a pre-determined oblivion while drinking 40s and smoking kush.
						</blockquote>
